-- W-fallthrough (ref-mode): a multi-clause fn whose FIRST clause is a guard chain
-- that can fail (n <= 10) and fall through to a later catch-all clause.  Returning a
-- String forces the §8.6 uniform (ref eq) rep, exercising the ref-mode clause-chain
-- fall-through path (the path the 261 self-host census gaps live in).  Hits both the
-- matched-guard path ("big") and the fall-through-to-next-clause path ("small").
classify n | n > 10 = "big"
classify n = "small"

main = classify 20 ++ classify 3
